<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>It was a comfortable night at the office for Graham Potter's side as they overcame Portsmouth 4-0 on Thursday in the Carabao Cup second round.</p>

<p>Alexis Mac Allister gave Brighton the lead in the 38th minute before Alireza Jahanbakhsh doubled that advantage inside 10 minutes of the second half.</p>

<p>Then Brighton strolled to victory as Bernardo and Viktor Gyokeres both added goals of their own at the Amex Stadium to seal their progression to the third round. </p>

<p>More to follow... </p>

<p>Bernardo netted Brighton's third of the night as the hosts ran riot against Portsmouth</p>
